sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Suspicious DotNET CLR Usage Log Artifact
sigma_analysis_results.rule_description: Detects the creation of Usage Log files by the CLR (clr.dll). These files are named after the executing process once the assembly is finished executing for the first time in the (user) session context.

Adversaries may abuse msiexec.exe to proxy execution of malicious payloads.
Msiexec.exe is the command-line utility for the Windows Installer and is thus commonly associated with executing installation packages (.msi)

match_context.values: @{Product=Windows Installer - Unicode; CurrentDirectory=C:\Windows\TEMP\; OriginalFileName=msiexec.exe; Hashes=SHA1=0C01E942244F1ED095D5EC92DA2FA043565C5CDD,MD5=D3C21CD0C70DC36FDD8A61E4517A226D,SHA256=D7A94CE4C50764B8A6F67DB308F8609AC38F08D1113079EAF81A25AB44E72BA6,IMPHASH=13C7ACE23F99CD5FBC3ABD5C16BF2DCE; Description=Windows\xae installer; EventID=1; ParentCommandLine="C:\Program Files (x86)\ATERA Networks\AteraAgent\Packages\AgentPackageUpgradeAgent\AgentPackageUpgradeAgent.exe" ab6d53a9-549b-40c7-aaaf-f65cb952582a "8db9a60c-3bef-4f4f-9c6b-4e4d1b91438a" agent-api.atera.com/Production 443 or8ixLi90Mf "checkforupdates" 001Q300000GLhlZIAT; CommandLine="msiexec.exe" /i C:\Windows\TEMP\ateraAgentSetup64_1_8_7_2.msi /lv* AteraSetupLog.txt /qn /norestart; FileVersion=5.0.17134.228 (WinBuild.160101.0800); ParentImage=C:\Program Files (x86)\ATERA Networks\AteraAgent\Packages\AgentPackageUpgradeAgent\AgentPackageUpgradeAgent.exe; IntegrityLevel=System; Image=C:\Windows\System32\msiexec.exe; Company=Microsoft Corporation}

sigma_analysis_results.rule_title: Unsigned DLL Loaded by Windows Utility
